<title type="html"><![CDATA[Books Recommended by Shaykh Ahmed an-Najmee in Tawheed &amp; ‘Aqeedah]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=570&amp;p=612#p612"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: normal"><span style="color: #0000FF">Books Recommended by Shaykh Ahmed an-Najmee in Tawheed &amp; ‘Aqeedah</span></span></strong><br /><br /><span style="color: #FF0000">Question:</span><br /><br />What are the books that you advise studying in the realm of Tawheed and ‘Aqeedah?<br /><br /><span style="color: #FF0000">Answer:</span><br /><br />The first of them is <span style="color: #0000FF">‘Kitaab at-Tawheed’</span> and <span style="color: #0000FF">‘Usool uth-Thalaatah’</span> and <span style="color: #0000FF">‘al-Qawaaid al-‘Arba’a’</span>, <span style="color: #0000FF">‘Kashfu Shubuhaat’</span> and the books of Shaykh ul-Islaam ibn Taymiyyah upon the subject of the Names and Attributes (of Allaah). The books of Shaykh Muhammad bin Abdul Wahaab and his children and grandchildren and students. Then those (books) after them, like <span style="color: #0000FF">‘Tawheed’</span> of ibn Khuzaymah and <span style="color: #0000FF">‘ar-Rad ‘alal-Jahmiyyah’</span> of ‘Uthmaan bin Sa’eed ad-Darimee, <span style="color: #0000FF">‘al-Ibaanahtul Kubraa’</span> and <span style="color: #0000FF">‘(al-Ibaanahtu) Sughraa’</span> of ibn Battah, <span style="color: #0000FF">‘Sharh Usool I’tiqaad Ahlus Sunnah’</span> by Laalikaaee, and (there are) many books other than them.<br /><br /><em>Taken From Daarul Minhaaj, p.182.</em><br />Shaykh Ahmad bin Yahyaa an-Najmee<br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://salaf-us-saalih.com/2014/01/15/booksahmadannajmee/">http://salaf-us-saalih.com/2014/01/15/b ... dannajmee/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Sat Nov 05, 2016 9:16 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
